quran[29]{c,v,t,f}:
  77,49,"Woe, that Day, to the deniers."
  77,50,"Then in what statement after it [i.e., the Qur’ān] will they believe?"
  79,40,"But as for he who feared the position of his Lord{1} and prevented the soul from [unlawful] inclination,",1:[See footnote to 55:46]
  79,41,"Then indeed, Paradise will be [his] refuge."
  79,42,"They ask you, [O Muḥammad], about the Hour: when is its arrival?{1}",1:[Literally, "resting" or "establishment."]
  80,37,"For every man, that Day, will be a matter adequate for him.{1}",1:[i.e., to occupy him. He will be concerned only with himself, thus forgetting all others.]
  80,38,"[Some] faces, that Day, will be bright -"
  80,39,"Laughing, rejoicing at good news."
  83,25,"They will be given to drink [pure] wine{1} [which was] sealed.",1:[Which is delicious and does not intoxicate.]
  83,26,"The last of it{1} is musk. So for this let the competitors compete.",1:[i.e., its lingering odor.]
  83,27,"And its mixture is of Tasneem,{1}",1:[The highest spring in Paradise and the most favored drink of its inhabitants.]
  84,22,"But those who have disbelieved deny,"
  84,23,"And Allāh is most knowing of what they keep within themselves."
  84,24,"So give them tidings of a painful punishment,"
  85,19,"But they who disbelieve are in [persistent] denial,"
  85,20,"While Allāh encompasses them from behind.{1}",1:[See footnote to 2:19]
  85,21,"But this is an honored Qur’ān"
  86,13,"Indeed, it [i.e., the Qur’ān] is a decisive statement,"
  86,14,"And it is not amusement."
  86,15,"Indeed, they are planning a plan,"
  87,10,"He who fears [Allāh] will be reminded."
  87,11,"But the wretched one will avoid it"
  87,12,"[He] who will [enter and] burn in the greatest Fire,"
  88,7,"Which neither nourishes nor avails against hunger."
  88,8,"[Other] faces, that Day, will show pleasure."
  88,9,"With their effort [they are] satisfied"
  89,4,"And [by] the night when it passes,"
  89,5,"Is there [not] in [all] that an oath [sufficient] for one of perception?{1}",1:[Based upon the following verses, what has been sworn to by Allāh is that He will certainly punish the disbelievers.]
  89,6,"Have you not considered how your Lord dealt with ʿAad -"